Contribution Guidelines
Thank you for considering contributing to our project! We welcome contributions from everyone, and this document outlines how you can get involved.

Ways to Contribute
There are several ways you can contribute to this project:

Reporting Bugs: If you encounter any issues or bugs while using the project, please report them by opening a GitHub issue.
Suggesting Enhancements: If you have ideas for enhancements or new features, feel free to suggest them by opening a GitHub issue.
Contributing Code: You can contribute directly by fixing bugs, implementing new features, or improving existing ones through pull requests.
Getting Started
If you're new to contributing to open-source projects or to our project specifically, here's how you can get started:

Fork the Repository: Fork the project repository to your GitHub account.
Clone the Repository: Clone your forked repository to your local machine using git clone.
Install Dependencies: Make sure to install any project dependencies according to the instructions in the README file.
Check Issues: Look through the existing GitHub issues to see if there's anything you can help with.
Create a Branch: Before making any changes, create a new branch for your work using git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name.
Make Changes: Make your desired changes to the codebase.
Test Changes: Test your changes thoroughly to ensure they work as expected.
Commit Changes: Once you're happy with your changes, commit them using descriptive commit messages.
Push Changes: Push your changes to your forked repository on GitHub using git push origin feature/your-feature-name.
Open a Pull Request: Finally, open a pull request on the original repository, detailing the changes you've made and any relevant information.
Code Style Guidelines
Please adhere to the following code style guidelines when contributing code:

Follow the existing code formatting conventions.
Use descriptive variable and function names.
Write clear and concise comments to explain complex logic.
Maintain consistency with the existing codebase.
Review Process
All pull requests will be reviewed by project maintainers. Feedback may be provided, and changes may be requested before a pull request is accepted.

Code of Conduct
Please review our Code of Conduct before contributing to ensure a positive and inclusive community experience.

License
By contributing to this project, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the project's LICENSE.
